This paper is about cross-lingual dependency parsing, which is a natural language processing task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, such as Lagrangian relaxation and posterior regularization, which are commonly used in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of corpus linguistic statistics to guide the inference process, which could fall under the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of graph-based dependency parsing, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper could also be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) if the cross-lingual dependency parsing is applied to image captioning or other visual tasks.
